<subSubSection id="01C865623C3D1232C0E6FDFDFAE2F6E3" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="496D36E93C3D1232C0E6FDFDFAE2F6E3" blockId="3.[151,532,1974,1999]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,153,539]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="69C211C73C3D1232C0E6FDFDFAE2F6E3" infered="true" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="153" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicName id="8ED24D6A3C3D1235C0E6FDFDFD82F0FF" authority="Knisch, 1920: 57" authorityName="Knisch" authorityPageNumber="57" authorityYear="1920" box="[151,528,1974,1999]" class="Aves" family="Apodidae" genus="Hydrochous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Apodiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="drakei">
<emphasis id="7BA6EAFB3C3D1235C0E6FDFDFECBF0FF" box="[151,345,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="152">Hydrochous drakei</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="F9BA3CB43C3D1235C12EFDFCFD82F0FF" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2460219440" box="[351,528,1974,1999]" collectionCode="RBINS" collectorName="Coll. R. I. Sc. N. B. Bras. Corumba &amp; P. D. Perkins &amp; P. D. Perkins." determinerName="A. d'Orchymont &amp; J. L. Hellman" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" specimenCount="8" typeStatus="syntype">
<treatmentCitation id="C87310F83C3D1235C12EFDFCFD82F0FF" author="Knisch, A." box="[351,528,1974,1999]" page="57" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" year="1920">
<bibRefCitation id="2D434B183C3D1235C12EFDFCFD82F0FF" author="Knisch, A." box="[351,528,1974,1999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="152" pagination="55 - 89" refId="ref5572" refString="Knisch, A. (1920) Die exotischen Hydrophiliden des Deutschen Entomologischen Museum (Col.). Archiv fur Naturegeschichte, 85 A, 55 - 89." type="journal article" year="1920">Knisch, 1920: 57</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
</materialsCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The RBINS kindly provided sixteen 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C25CFAD3FD1DF783" box="[557,655,153,179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="8ED24D6A3C3A1232C2C2FAD3FC40F783" authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[691,978,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drakei">
<emphasis id="7BA6EAFB3C3A1232C2C2FAD3FCE8F783" box="[691,890,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Hydrochus drakei</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
, which are part of the Orchymont/Knisch types collection. The 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C1FFFAF7FE62F7E7" box="[398,496,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">syntypes</typeStatus>
consist of five males, ten females, and one specimen of unknown gender (a prior worker dissected the specimen, but there are no apical genital segments or male genitalia with the specimen). All five males have been dissected, and are conspecific. The females appear to also represent the same species. I have selected one of the males to serve as 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C249FB63FD30F673" box="[568,674,297,323]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">lectotype</typeStatus>
, have labeled it such, and provide images of the habitus, male genitalia and labels of this specimen (
<figureCitation id="D1E92A6C3C3A1232C264FB07FDF6F657" box="[533,612,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1623,1648]" captionTargetBox="[176,1425,204,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,181,1597]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hydrochus drakei Knisch, habitus and male genitalia of lectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557933/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D1E92A6C3C3A1232C202FB07FD37F657" box="[627,677,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1980,2005]" captionTargetBox="[215,1415,381,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[158,1430,381,1955]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Labels of lectotypes. (A) Hydrochus ducalis Knisch; (B) Hydrochus drakei Knisch; (C) Hydrochus variabilis Knisch; (D) Hydrochus corruscans Bruch; (E) Hydrochus argutus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557951/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">12B</figureCitation>
). 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C2CBFB07FCB8F657" box="[698,810,333,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Lectotype</typeStatus>
labels (
<figureCitation id="D1E92A6C3C3A1232C3F5FB07FC7EF657" box="[900,1004,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 12" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1980,2005]" captionTargetBox="[215,1415,381,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[158,1430,381,1955]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 12A–E. Labels of lectotypes. (A) Hydrochus ducalis Knisch; (B) Hydrochus drakei Knisch; (C) Hydrochus variabilis Knisch; (D) Hydrochus corruscans Bruch; (E) Hydrochus argutus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557951/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
): “ 
<collectorName id="E427533F3C3A1232C47CFB07FA0EF657" box="[1037,1436,333,359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Coll. R. I. Sc. N. B. Bras.Corumba</collectorName>
[Matto Grosso] // 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C110FB3BFE51F6BB" box="[353,451,369,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Paratype</typeStatus>
// Ex Coll. et det. 
<determinerName id="BCB1DA2D3C3A1232C2E1FB3BFCD5F6BB" box="[656,839,369,395]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">A.d’Orchymont</determinerName>
: R.M.H.N.B. 15.962 // 
<taxonomicName id="8ED24D6A3C3A1232C43CFB3BFAF9F6BB" authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[1101,1387,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drakei">Hydrochus drakei Knisch</taxonomicName>
det. 
<determinerName id="BCB1DA2D3C3A1232C0E6FBDFFEB0F69F" box="[151,290,405,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">J.L.Hellman</determinerName>
// HABITUS/GENIT. DIGITAL IMAGES captured 2019 
<collectorName id="E427533F3C3A1232C3C8FBDFFBD6F69F" box="[953,1092,405,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">P.D. Perkins</collectorName>
// [red] 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C4D5FBDFFAD6F69F" box="[1188,1348,405,431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName id="8ED24D6A3C3A1232C53DFBDFFEFDF6E3" authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drakei">
<emphasis id="7BA6EAFB3C3A1232C53DFBDFFE88F6E3" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Hydrochus drakei</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
desig. 
<collectorName id="E427533F3C3A1232C1CEFBF3FDC8F6E3" box="[447,602,441,467]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">P. D. Perkins.</collectorName>
” The fifteen non-lectotype 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C3FFFBF3FC62F6E3" box="[910,1008,441,467]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">syntypes</typeStatus>
have been labeled 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C4B7FBF3FAF9F6E3" box="[1222,1387,441,467]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="01C865623C3A1232C0B6FB97FC65F52B" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="496D36E93C3A1232C0B6FB97FC65F52B" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="7BA6EAFB3C3A1232C0B6FB97FEA9F6C7" bold="true" box="[199,315,477,503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Remarks.</emphasis>
One of the 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C1B5FB97FDB4F6C7" box="[452,550,477,503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">syntypes</typeStatus>
bears a 
<typeStatus id="9669884B3C3A1232C2F7FB97FD7FF6C7" box="[646,749,477,503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">lectotype</typeStatus>
label, by J. L. Hellman, but this designation was never published. This label has been reversed and “unpub.” written on the reverse side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
